---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Breadcrumb, PageNav, Callout } from '../../components/docs';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Inclusions"
  description="Learn about diagnostic inclusions and fingerprinting techniques for gem identification."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <Breadcrumb items={[
      { label: 'Learn', href: '/learn' },
      { label: 'Inclusions' }
    ]} />

    <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <h1>Inclusions in Gemstones</h1>

      <p class="lead">
        Inclusions are internal features that provide valuable information about a gem's
        identity, origin, and natural vs. synthetic status. They are a gem's "fingerprint."
      </p>

      <h2>Types of Inclusions</h2>

      <h3>Solid Inclusions</h3>

      <p>Crystals of other minerals trapped during growth:</p>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Host Gem</th>
            <th>Common Solid Inclusions</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Ruby/Sapphire</td>
            <td>Rutile silk, zircon halos, calcite, apatite</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Emerald</td>
            <td>Pyrite, calcite, tremolite, mica, chromite</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Diamond</td>
            <td>Garnet, olivine, chromite, graphite</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Peridot</td>
            <td>Chromite (black crystals), "lily pad" inclusions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Garnet</td>
            <td>Rutile, apatite, rounded crystals</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Fluid Inclusions</h3>

      <p>Trapped liquids, often with gas bubbles:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Two-phase</strong> - Liquid + gas bubble</li>
        <li><strong>Three-phase</strong> - Liquid + gas + solid crystal (diagnostic for Colombian emerald)</li>
        <li><strong>Fingerprint inclusions</strong> - Healed fractures with fluid remnants</li>
        <li><strong>Negative crystals</strong> - Fluid-filled cavities with crystal shape</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Growth Features</h3>

      <p>Patterns formed during crystallization:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Colour zoning</strong> - Bands of different colour intensity</li>
        <li><strong>Growth tubes</strong> - Hollow channels parallel to c-axis</li>
        <li><strong>Twinning</strong> - Internal reflection planes</li>
        <li><strong>Phantoms</strong> - Earlier growth stages visible inside</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Diagnostic Inclusions by Species</h2>

      <h3>Corundum (Ruby and Sapphire)</h3>

      <div class="not-prose grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Burmese Ruby</h4>
          <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Short rutile silk (fine needles)</li>
            <li>Calcite crystals</li>
            <li>"Swirl" growth patterns</li>
            <li>Flux fingerprints (if heated)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Kashmir Sapphire</h4>
          <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Tourmaline crystals</li>
            <li>Zircon with tension halos</li>
            <li>"Milky" zones (fine particles)</li>
            <li>Colour zoning</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Thai/Cambodian Ruby</h4>
          <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Dense rutile silk networks</li>
            <li>Iron-stained fractures</li>
            <li>Dark iron-rich crystals</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Sri Lankan Sapphire</h4>
          <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Long rutile silk</li>
            <li>Zircon halos</li>
            <li>Colour zoning (hexagonal)</li>
            <li>Negative crystals</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Emerald</h3>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Origin</th>
            <th>Characteristic Inclusions</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Colombia</td>
            <td>Three-phase inclusions (liquid + gas + halite cube), calcite rhombs</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Zambia</td>
            <td>Black mica flakes, amphibole needles, blocky crystals</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Brazil</td>
            <td>Biotite mica, pyrite, two-phase inclusions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Afghanistan</td>
            <td>Mica books, actinolite needles</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Other Gemstones</h3>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Gemstone</th>
            <th>Diagnostic Inclusions</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Peridot</td>
            <td>"Lily pad" discoid fractures, black chromite crystals</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Spinel</td>
            <td>Octahedral negative crystals, "fingerprint" inclusions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Aquamarine</td>
            <td>Rain-like parallel tubes, two-phase inclusions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Tourmaline</td>
            <td>Growth tubes parallel to c-axis, trichites</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Topaz</td>
            <td>Two-phase inclusions, cleavage cracks</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Amethyst</td>
            <td>Zebra stripes (colour zoning), tiger stripes</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Natural vs. Synthetic Indicators</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">Natural Indicators</h4>
            <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-emerald-800">
              <li>Mineral crystal inclusions</li>
              <li>Three-phase inclusions</li>
              <li>Fingerprint patterns</li>
              <li>Irregular colour zoning</li>
              <li>Natural growth patterns</li>
              <li>Stress fractures around crystals</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900">Synthetic Indicators</h4>
            <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-amber-800">
              <li>Curved striae (flame fusion)</li>
              <li>Gas bubbles (flame fusion)</li>
              <li>Flux inclusions (flux growth)</li>
              <li>Chevron/zigzag zoning (hydrothermal)</li>
              <li>Seed plates (hydrothermal)</li>
              <li>Platinum/gold flakes (flux)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Microscopy Techniques</h2>

      <p>
        Different lighting techniques reveal different inclusion types:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Darkfield</strong> - Best for seeing inclusions against dark background</li>
        <li><strong>Brightfield</strong> - Good for colour zoning and growth patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Fibre-optic</strong> - Pinpoint light for specific features</li>
        <li><strong>Immersion</strong> - Reduces surface reflections, reveals internal features</li>
        <li><strong>Polarized light</strong> - Shows strain patterns and twinning</li>
      </ul>

      <Callout variant="tip" title="Best Practice">
        <p>
          Always examine gems under magnification (10x minimum, 40-60x preferred)
          using multiple lighting techniques. Document findings with photographs
          when possible for comparison and records.
        </p>
      </Callout>
    </article>

    <PageNav
      prev={{ label: 'Optical Properties', href: '/learn/optical-properties' }}
      next={{ label: 'Treatments', href: '/learn/treatments' }}
    />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
